<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She welcomed her 'miracle' baby boy in March this year after being given only one per cent chance of conceiving.</p>

<p>And Nadia Essex was the picture of a doting mother as she cradled son Ezekiel in her arms before taking him with her in his stroller as she got her hair done in London on Friday afternoon.</p>

<p>The TV personality, 38, was seen getting her highlights done at the Ozzie Rizzo Richmond salon, and she and the hairdresser wore a mask to make sure they kept safe amid the coronavirus crisis.</p>

<p>Sweet: Nadia Essex was every inch the doting mother as she cradled son Ezekiel and put him in his carrier before getting her hair done at a salon in London on Friday</p>

<p>As the hairdressers got to work on her hair, Nadia was seen looking at her phone as her little one relaxed in his carrier beside her.</p>

<p>Nadia looked casually chic in a red striped longline jacket, which she shrugged on over a black tank top.</p>

<p>She completed her look with a pair of straight-cut jeans, while she stepped out in a pair of white trainers.</p>

<p>Safety first: The TV personality, 38, was seen getting her highlights done at the Ozzie Rizzo Richmond salon, and she and the hairdresser wore a mask</p>

<p>Catching up: As the hairdressers got to work on her hair, Nadia was seen looking at her phone as her little one relaxed in his carrier beside her</p>

<p>Stylish: Nadia looked casually chic in a red striped longline jacket, which she shrugged on over a black tank top</p>

<p>Doting: Nadia cooed over Ezekiel after she had her hair done, and her little one looked relaxed in his carrier as they returned to her car</p>

<p>Sweet: Nadia held onto her son tightly as she went to put him in his baby seat</p>

<p> In July, Nadia shared a candid Instagram snap of herself taken five days after giving birth to son Ezekiel.</p>

<p>The TV star welcomed her first child in March, and shared the photo to celebrate his three month milestone.</p>

<p>Nadia also posted the candid snap, which shows her sobbing, in a bid to show the 'true face of motherhood'. </p>

<p>The dating guru explained in the caption that at the time she was 'in bits' and 'overwhelmed' at being a new mother and alone during the COVID-19 lockdown. </p>

<p>Appointment: The hairstylist put Nadia's hair in curlers and foil</p>

<p>Finishing touches: Nadia completed her look with a pair of straight-cut jeans, while she stepped out in a pair of white trainers</p>

<p>Before: Nadia was seen without her mask briefly as she spoke with a person in the salon</p>

<p>Stunning: Nadia's hairdressers styled her golden locks in chic waves</p>

<p>Goodies: Nadia appeared to have bought herself some hair-styling products from the salon</p>

<p>Nadia is co-parenting with her baby's father, who lives in the US, and has sworn to keep his identity a secret.</p>

<p>The television personality, who had been given only a one per cent chance of conceiving, also shared that she is 'proud to have done it alone'.</p>

<p>Nadia penned: 'The true face of motherhood. It's not pretty but it's real and it's ok! Today is Zeeks 3 month birthday and this taken 5 days after he was born and I was in bits. </p>

<p>East does it: Nadia was careful as she pushed Ezekiel's stroller out of the salon</p>

<p>Heading home: Nadia was seen putting her shopping bag in the back of her car</p>

<p>'There was a killer virus, I was going to have to go into lockdown alone and it was very difficult to not feel overwhelmed on top of the usual craziness of being a new, first time mum. </p>

<p>'Since then you have grown into the most wonderful boy. I am absolutely grateful and amazed that you are my son.'</p>

<p>Nadia went on to lament the fact single mothers are often seen as inferior to single fathers. </p>

<p>'The true face of motherhood': In July, Nadia shared a candid snap of herself taken five days after giving birth to son Ezekiel to Instagram</p>

<p>Sweet: The TV star welcomed her first child in March, and shared the photo to celebrate his three month milestone</p>

<p>She continued: 'Often single mothers are thought of as trash and single fathers as hero's. I am so proud to be your mummy. Proud to have done it alone. Proud we are a team and proud you are my best friend. </p>

<p>'If you feel like this remember it's ok. All the 'perfect' mums on SM have had these days too. Know that these feelings pass, things get easier and you will be ok. Sending love and strength to everyone who needs it ❤️.' </p>

<p>It comes after Nadia revealed she's shed a total of seven pounds in just a month by using the DoTheUnthinkable fitness plan after adopting a healthy lifestyle since Ezekiel was born.</p>

<p>In a candid Instagram post, the star showcased her four-week progress with side-by-side images of herself at the start of her fitness programme and her current appearance.</p>

<p>Speaking out: Nadia also posted the candid snap, which shows her sobbing, in a bid to show the 'true face of motherhood'</p>

<p>To highlight her transformation, the media personality wore the same outfit in both photos - a fuschia pink crop top and plain black briefs. </p>

<p>The reality star detailed her weight loss journey as she captioned the photo: 'One month down of my <?php echo e('@'); ?>dotheunthinkableuk plan, I’m 7lbs down and feel b***dy fabulous.</p>

<p>'Truly enjoying this plan!! The food is delicious and I’m starting to workout with <?php echo e('@'); ?>steve.ahern &amp; move more which I know is helping me feel good and keep me healthy. </p>

<p>'Two more months to go and soooo excited to see what I can achieve in that time. Use my code NADIA10 for £10 off your first week ❤️ #dotheunthinkable #weightlossjourney #dietplan #ad #workout #healthylifestyle #healthiswealth.' [sic]</p>

